stylometry:
Tradeoff - with ordering inventory there are 2 very distinct tradeoffs: ordering costs and holding costs. If you order large amounts infrequently, you will incur large amounts of holding costs. Alternatively if you order small amounts frequently, you will have larger ordering costs. By using models you must decide what the best number and size of orders is ideal for minimizing costs.

EOQ - Stands for Economic Order Quantity. The point of this quantity is to find the best number and size of the order, hence the most economic option. This equalizes the tradeoff between ordering and holding costs.
